    "id": "662",
    "title": "Solitary Pulmonary Nodule (SPN) Malignancy Risk Score (Mayo Clinic Model)",
    "desc": "The Solitary Pulmonary Nodule (SPN) Malignancy Risk Score predicts malignancy risk in solitary lung nodules on chest x-ray.",
    "data": {
        "orgreference": [
            {
                "href": "https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9129544 ",
                "text": "Swensen SJ, Silverstein MD, Ilstrup DM, Schleck CD, Edell ES. The probability of malignancy in solitary pulmonary nodules. Application to small radiologically indeterminate nodules. Arch Intern Med. 1997;157(8):849-55."
            }
        ],
        "other_refer": [
            {
                "href": "https://annals.org/aim/fullarticle/716394/cost-effectiveness-alternative-management-strategies-patients-solitary-pulmonary-nodules",
                "text": "Gould MK, Sanders GD, Barnett PG, et al. Cost-effectiveness of alternative management strategies for patients with solitary pulmonary nodules. Ann Intern Med. 2003;138(9):724-35."
            }
        ],
        "evidence": "<p>Probability of malignancy, % = 100 x e<sup>x&nbsp;</sup>/ (1 + e<sup>x</sup>)</p>\n<p>Probability of malignancy with FDG-PET, % = 100 / (1 + e<sup>-y</sup>)</p>\n<p>where:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>x&nbsp;= (0.0391 &times; age, years) + (0.1274 &times; nodule diameter, mm) + (0.7917 &times; smoker) + (1.3388 &times; cancer) + (0.7838 &times; upper lobe) + (1.0407 &times; spiculation) - 6.8272,&nbsp;</li>\n<li>y&nbsp;= -4.739 + (3.691 &times; probability of malignancy*)&nbsp;+ 2.322 (if faint uptake), or + 4.617 (if moderate uptake), or + 4.771 (if intense uptake),</li>\n</ul>\n<p>and other variables are as follows:</p>\n<table><colgroup><col width=\"231\" /><col width=\"75\" /><col width=\"56\" /></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Variable</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Points</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Current or former smoker</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">No</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">0</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Extrathoracic cancer diagnosis &ge;5 years prior</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">No</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">0</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Upper lobe location of tumor</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">No</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">0</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Nodule spiculation</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">No</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">0</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-869c11dc-7fff-dce1-2584-fd53295bb2a3\">*Note: expressed as a decimal, e.g. 0.12 for 12%.</span></p>",
        "facts": "",
